strings.Value: "Do I have time to look around?"
"Well, Cephal? Has your magic worked? It doesn't look like anything changed."
"Yes. The gates will open in a moment or two. Be ready!"
"The faithful have nothing to fear in the Master's citadel! Except, perhaps, a dead cyclops emperor and his servants, who have no wish to cede His gift, though it was never truly theirs to claim."
"... has it really begun? Well, Torag bless you in all your deeds and ways. So long!"

{n}Kjerdi's last words are drowned out by a dull moan that rises over the area. The doors of the ancient dungeon slowly open, as if a huge creature is opening its maw. The path in front of you lies open.{/n}
"Keep your weapons and spells at the ready. We don't know what awaits us inside."
{n}Cephal frowns.{/n} "Yes, but very little. Get on with it."
